🔍 SHAP Explainability Analysis

SHAP analysis demonstrated that age and nuclear morphometric features were the primary drivers of model predictions.

Most influential variables:

Age
Nuclear perimeter
Nuclear eccentricity
Nuclear area

Age was the dominant predictor for:

Haematolymphoid tumours
Mesenchymal tumours
Neuroectodermal / neural crest-derived tumours

Nuclear perimeter was the strongest predictor for melanocytic tumours.

Sex and most anatomical site variables showed minimal influence on model decisions.

